 By Evelyn Usman and Esther Onyegbula, Lagos A 54-year old woman who acted as a midwife at the baby factory in the Ijegun area of Lagos state, Sherifat Ipaye, disclosed that she collected N15,000 for each delivery, while her partner in crime, Happiness Ukwuoma was paid N20,000 monthly, with free accommodation. Her job specification according to her, was to take care of the ladies and move them to Ipaye’s place whenever they were due for delivery. Continue reading Baby factory: I collected N15,000 for each delivery ― “Nurse” at Vanguard Nigeria. Source: Vanguard